name: tan
description: Returns the tangent of a number.

name: sqrt
description: Returns the square root of a number.

name: trim
description: Trims the specified trim string from the start and end of a string. If no trim string is provided, all whitespace is removed from the start and end of the input string.

name: log10
description: Returns the base-10 logarithm of a number.

name: nvl
description: Returns _expression2_ if _expression1_ is NULL otherwise it returns _expression1_.

name: char_length
description: Returns the number of characters in a string.

name: radians
description: Converts degrees to radians.

name: ln
description: Returns the natural logarithm of a number.

name: bool_or
description: Returns true if all non-null input values are true, otherwise false.

name: nth_value
description: Returns the value evaluated at the nth row of the window frame (counting from 1). Returns NULL if no such row exists.

name: regexp_replace
description: Replaces substrings in a string that match a [regular expression](https://docs.rs/regex/latest/regex/#syntax).

name: date_format
description: Returns a string representation of a date, time, timestamp or duration based on a [Chrono format](https://docs.rs/chrono/latest/chrono/format/strftime/index.html). Unlike the PostgreSQL equivalent of this function numerical formatting is not supported.

name: substr
description: Extracts a substring of a specified number of characters from a specific starting position in a string.

name: ascii
description: Returns the Unicode character code of the first character in a string.

name: regexp_instr
description: Returns the position in a string where the specified occurrence of a POSIX regular expression is located.

name: character_length
description: Returns the number of characters in a string.

name: var_samp
description: Returns the statistical sample variance of a set of numbers.

name: var_pop
description: Returns the statistical population variance of a set of numbers.

name: array_agg
description:
Returns an array created from the expression elements. If ordering is required, elements are inserted in the specified order.
This aggregation function can only mix DISTINCT and ORDER BY if the ordering expression is exactly the same as the argument expression.

name: floor
description: Returns the nearest integer less than or equal to a number.

name: strpos
description: Returns the starting position of a specified substring in a string. Positions begin at 1. If the substring does not exist in the string, the function returns 0.

name: md5
description: Computes an MD5 128-bit checksum for a string expression.

name: signum
description:
Returns the sign of a number.
Negative numbers return `-1`.
Zero and positive numbers return `1`.

name: date_trunc
description: Truncates a timestamp value to a specified precision.

name: lower
description: Converts a string to lower-case.

name: length
description: Returns the number of characters in a string.

name: chr
description: Returns the character with the specified ASCII or Unicode code value.

name: greatest
description: Returns the greatest value in a list of expressions. Returns _null_ if all expressions are _null_.

name: reverse
description: Reverses the character order of a string.

name: cot
description: Returns the cotangent of a number.

name: power
description: Returns a base expression raised to the power of an exponent.

name: min
description: Returns the minimum value in the specified column.

name: bit_xor
description: Computes the bitwise exclusive OR of all non-null input values.

name: avg
description: Returns the average of numeric values in the specified column.

name: stddev_samp
description: Returns the standard deviation of a set of numbers.

name: sum
description: Returns the sum of all values in the specified column.

name: bit_or
description: Computes the bitwise OR of all non-null input values.

name: last_value
description: Returns value evaluated at the row that is the last row of the window frame.

name: round
description: Rounds a number to the nearest integer.

name: asin
description: Returns the arc sine or inverse sine of a number.

name: upper
description: Converts a string to upper-case.

name: position
description: Returns the starting position of a specified substring in a string. Positions begin at 1. If the substring does not exist in the string, the function returns 0.

name: atan2
description: Returns the arc tangent or inverse tangent of `expression_y / expression_x`.

name: acos
description: Returns the arc cosine or inverse cosine of a number.

name: right
description: Returns a specified number of characters from the right side of a string.

name: left
description: Returns a specified number of characters from the left side of a string.

name: first_value
description: Returns value evaluated at the row that is the first row of the window frame.

name: datetrunc
description: Truncates a timestamp value to a specified precision.

name: current_timestamp
description:
Returns the current UTC timestamp.

The `now()` return value is determined at query time and will return the same timestamp, no matter when in the query plan the function executes.

name: find_in_set
description: Returns a value in the range of 1 to N if the string str is in the string list strlist consisting of N substrings.

name: to_hex
description: Converts an integer to a hexadecimal string.

name: octet_length
description: Returns the length of a string in bytes.

name: nullif
description:
Returns _null_ if _expression1_ equals _expression2_; otherwise it returns _expression1_.
This can be used to perform the inverse operation of [`coalesce`](#coalesce).

name: replace
description: Replaces all occurrences of a specified substring in a string with a new substring.

name: today
description:
Returns the current UTC date.

The `current_date()` return value is determined at query time and will return the same date, no matter when in the query plan the function executes.

name: substring
description: Extracts a substring of a specified number of characters from a specific starting position in a string.

name: last_value
description: Returns the last element in an aggregation group according to the requested ordering. If no ordering is given, returns an arbitrary element from the group.

name: nth_value
description: Returns the nth value in a group of values.

name: instr
description: Returns the starting position of a specified substring in a string. Positions begin at 1. If the substring does not exist in the string, the function returns 0.

name: coalesce
description: Returns the first of its arguments that is not _null_. Returns _null_ if all arguments are _null_. This function is often used to substitute a default value for _null_ values.

name: concat
description: Concatenates multiple strings together.

name: from_unixtime
description: Converts an integer to RFC3339 timestamp format (`YYYY-MM-DDT00:00:00.000000000Z`). Integers and unsigned integers are interpreted as seconds since the unix epoch (`1970-01-01T00:00:00Z`) return the corresponding timestamp.

name: log2
description: Returns the base-2 logarithm of a number.

name: ltrim
description: Trims the specified trim string from the beginning of a string. If no trim string is provided, all whitespace is removed from the start of the input string.

name: bit_length
description: Returns the bit length of a string.

name: abs
description: Returns the absolute value of a number.

name: ceil
description: Returns the nearest integer greater than or equal to a number.

name: cos
description: Returns the cosine of a number.

name: random
description:
Returns a random float value in the range [0, 1).
The random seed is unique to each row.

name: version
description: Returns the version of DataFusion.

name: rpad
description: Pads the right side of a string with another string to a specified string length.

name: rtrim
description: Trims the specified trim string from the end of a string. If no trim string is provided, all whitespace is removed from the end of the input string.

name: count
description: Returns the number of non-null values in the specified column. To include null values in the total count, use `count(*)`.

name: bit_and
description: Computes the bitwise AND of all non-null input values.

name: stddev_pop
description: Returns the population standard deviation of a set of numbers.

name: first_value
description: Returns the first element in an aggregation group according to the requested ordering. If no ordering is given, returns an arbitrary element from the group.

name: max
description: Returns the maximum value in the specified column.

name: stddev
description: Returns the standard deviation of a set of numbers.

name: percent_rank
description: Returns the percentage rank of the current row within its partition. The value ranges from 0 to 1 and is computed as `(rank - 1) / (total_rows - 1)`.

name: rank
description: Returns the rank of the current row within its partition, allowing gaps between ranks. This function provides a ranking similar to `row_number`, but skips ranks for identical values.

name: dense_rank
description: Returns the rank of the current row without gaps. This function ranks rows in a dense manner, meaning consecutive ranks are assigned even for identical values.

name: lead
description: Returns value evaluated at the row that is offset rows after the current row within the partition; if there is no such row, instead return default (which must be of the same type as value).

name: ntile
description: Integer ranging from 1 to the argument value, dividing the partition as equally as possible

name: atan
description: Returns the arc tangent or inverse tangent of a number.

name: uuid
description: Returns [`UUID v4`](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Universally_unique_identifier#Version_4_(random)) string value which is unique per row.

name: degrees
description: Converts radians to degrees.

name: sin
description: Returns the sine of a number.

name: now
description:
Returns the current UTC timestamp.

The `now()` return value is determined at query time and will return the same timestamp, no matter when in the query plan the function executes.

name: log
description: Returns the base-x logarithm of a number. Can either provide a specified base, or if omitted then takes the base-10 of a number.

name: least
description: Returns the smallest value in a list of expressions. Returns _null_ if all expressions are _null_.

name: current_time
description:
Returns the current UTC time.

The `current_time()` return value is determined at query time and will return the same time, no matter when in the query plan the function executes.

name: concat_ws
description: Concatenates multiple strings together with a specified separator.

name: pi
description: Returns an approximate value of Ï€.

name: substring_index
description:
Returns the substring from str before count occurrences of the delimiter delim.
If count is positive, everything to the left of the final delimiter (counting from the left) is returned.
If count is negative, everything to the right of the final delimiter (counting from the right) is returned.

name: nvl2
description: Returns _expression2_ if _expression1_ is not NULL; otherwise it returns _expression3_.

name: sha256
description: Computes the SHA-256 hash of a binary string.

name: sha512
description: Computes the SHA-512 hash of a binary string.

name: ifnull
description: Returns _expression2_ if _expression1_ is NULL otherwise it returns _expression1_.

name: regexp_like
description: Returns true if a [regular expression](https://docs.rs/regex/latest/regex/#syntax) has at least one match in a string, false otherwise.

name: exp
description: Returns the base-e exponential of a number.

name: lpad
description: Pads the left side of a string with another string to a specified string length.

name: repeat
description: Returns a string with an input string repeated a specified number.

name: to_char
description: Returns a string representation of a date, time, timestamp or duration based on a [Chrono format](https://docs.rs/chrono/latest/chrono/format/strftime/index.html). Unlike the PostgreSQL equivalent of this function numerical formatting is not supported.

name: pow
description: Returns a base expression raised to the power of an exponent.

name: current_date
description:
Returns the current UTC date.

The `current_date()` return value is determined at query time and will return the same date, no matter when in the query plan the function executes.

name: string_agg
description: Concatenates the values of string expressions and places separator values between them. If ordering is required, strings are concatenated in the specified order. This aggregation function can only mix DISTINCT and ORDER BY if the ordering expression is exactly the same as the first argument expression.

name: bool_and
description: Returns true if all non-null input values are true, otherwise false.

name: lag
description: Returns value evaluated at the row that is offset rows before the current row within the partition; if there is no such row, instead return default (which must be of the same type as value).

name: cume_dist
description: Relative rank of the current row: (number of rows preceding or peer with the current row) / (total rows).

name: row_number
description: Number of the current row within its partition, counting from 1.

name: if
description: Returns one value if a condition is TRUE, or another value if a condition is FALSE

name: ceiling
description: Returns the smallest integer value greater than or equal to a number

name: datediff
description: Returns the number of days between two dates

name: timestampdiff
description: Returns the difference between two datetime expressions

name: inet_aton
description: Converts an IPv4 address to numeric value

name: inet_ntoa
description: Converts numeric value to IPv4 address

name: format
description: Formats number to specified decimal places and adds thousand separators

name: hex
description: Returns hexadecimal representation of a decimal or string value

name: unhex
description: Converts hexadecimal value to string

name: lcase
description: Synonym for LOWER()

name: quote
description: Escapes string and adds single quotes

name: soundex
description: Returns soundex string of given string

name: space
description: Returns string of specified number of spaces

name: truncate
description: Truncates number to specified number of decimal places

name: weekday
description: Returns weekday index (0=Monday, 6=Sunday)

name: yearweek
description: Returns year and week number

name: dayname
description: Returns name of weekday

name: monthname
description: Returns name of month

name: quarter
description: Returns quarter from date (1 to 4)

name: week
description: Returns week number

name: group_concat
description: Returns a concatenated string from a group

name: std
description: Returns the population standard deviation

name: variance
description: Returns the population variance

name: json_arrayagg
description: Aggregates result set as JSON array

name: json_objectagg
description: Aggregates result set as JSON object
